    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen changing the buffer shown in a float window with `style = \"minimal\"`, the local value of a global-local option is lost. This is not the case in `0.11.6` and it may be a consequence of https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/5943a81fe79a0d9a639af88452050a5056e9027d .\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim repro.lua` where `repro.lua` contains the following\n\n```lua\n-- default (global?) value of `listchars` is printed\nprint(vim.wo.listchars)\n\nlocal buf1 = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(true, true)\nlocal buf2 = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(true, true)\nlocal minimal_win = vim.api.nvim_open_win(buf1, true, {\n\trelative = \"editor\",\n\trow = 0,\n\tcol = 0,\n\twidth = 10,\n\theight = 10,\n\tstyle = \"minimal\",\n})\nvim.api.nvim_set_option_value(\"listchars\", \"extends:…,precedes:…\", { scope = \"local\", win = minimal_win })\n-- new value (local) of `listchars` is printed\nprint(vim.wo.listchars)\n\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_buf(minimal_win, buf2)\n-- default (global?) value of `listchars` is printed\nprint(vim.wo.listchars)\n\n-- the previously set local value of `listcharts` should be printed, but the\n-- default (global?) one is used instead\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_buf(minimal_win, buf1)\nprint(vim.wo.listchars)\n```\n\n2. `:source`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe local value of global-local options (in this case `listchars`) should be remembered for floating windows with `style = \"minimal\"`. This is the behavior in `0.11.6`, but not in the nightly release\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2462+g1a02896e16\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch linux latest\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nwezterm\n\n### Installation\n\npacman",
