            "body": "Hmm, doesn't that patch allow values to leak in other cases? It also looks like it applies to non-minimal floats.\n\nAlso, I guess it should be noted that the regression doesn't only affect global-locals; also affects local values of regular winopts. E.g: HEAD forgets the local value of `'rightleft'`:\n\n```vim\nedit foo\ncall setline(1, 'foo')\ncall nvim_win_set_config(0, #{style: 'minimal'})\nsetlocal rightleft\nedit bar\nbuffer #\n```",
